        <head xml:id="pl-l4d3c6-Hd1e109">CAP. VI</head>
        <head xml:id="pl-l4d3c6-Hd1e112" type="question-title">
          Why it happens only in water
        </head>
        <p xml:id="pl-l4d3c6-d1e115">
          Moreover this sacrament is only celebrated in water, 
          not in any other liquid, 
          as Christ said: 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pl-l4d3c6-Qd1e119" ana="#io3_5">
              Unless one 
              was reborn from water
            </quote>
            <bibl>Iohannes 3:5</bibl>
          </cit>
          etc. 
          Therefore it is uniformly commanded 
          that occur in water, 
          as it is understood, 
          that 
          <cit>
            <quote xml:id="pl-l4d3c6-Qd1e117">
              just as water washes dirt from the body and garments, 
              so baptism cleanses 
              by removing stains on the soul 
              and the dirt of vices
            </quote>
            <bibl>XXX, <!-- comment. in espist. ad rom 6:4 (inter opera Ambrose) See PL 47,100 --></bibl>
          </cit>. 
          Or therefore for another reason, 
          namely so that nothing is excusable through poverty, 
          as would be the case if baptism 
          occurred using wine and oil, 
          and so that the common material for baptizing 
          would be found among all. 
          What water signified was that 
          which flowed from the side of Christ, 
          just as the blood of the other sacrament is a sign. 
          Therefore baptism is not able to be consecrated 
          in any other liquid besides water.
        </p>
